Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Arland D. Williams Jr. Memorial Bridge Overlook in Washington, D.C. She praised the work being done to rebuild infrastructure in America and highlighted the importance of investing in the country's bridges. Harris announced that nearly $300 million will be invested to repair nine critical bridges across the country, including the one behind her. She emphasized the impact that these repairs will have on improving transportation, reducing traffic, and ensuring the safety of drivers. Overall, Harris emphasized the importance of infrastructure investment in building a better future for all Americans.